      "text": "CRE Glossary – Key Terms for This Diagram",
      "originalText": "CRE Glossary – Key Terms for This Diagram",
      "lineHeight": 1.4
    },
    {
      "id": "t-gloss-b",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 55,
      "y": 1065,
      "width": 1650,
      "height": 108,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#212529",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 396923,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 82628,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1703000000000,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "text": "NOI (Net Operating Income):  Total revenue minus operating expenses, before debt service. The core metric for valuing income-producing real estate.\nCap Rate:  NOI / Property Value. Higher cap rate = more risk or less-premium market. Cap rate expansion = prices falling; compression = prices rising.\nDSCR (Debt Service Coverage Ratio):  NOI / Annual Debt Service. Lenders typically require >= 1.25x. Below 1.20x is a red flag for multifamily.\nOccupancy Rate:  Percentage of units currently rented. Below 90% in a stable market signals elevated risk.\nValue-add Business Plan:  Strategy to improve a property through renovations or management upgrades to raise rents and NOI, then sell at a higher valuation.\nGo / No-Go:  Final investment committee decision based on underwriting results, risk flag summary, and return targets vs. thresholds.",
      "originalText": "NOI (Net Operating Income):  Total revenue minus operating expenses, before debt service. The core metric for valuing income-producing real estate.\nCap Rate:  NOI / Property Value. Higher cap rate = more risk or less-premium market. Cap rate expansion = prices falling; compression = prices rising.\nDSCR (Debt Service Coverage Ratio):  NOI / Annual Debt Service. Lenders typically require >= 1.25x. Below 1.20x is a red flag for multifamily.\nOccupancy Rate:  Percentage of units currently rented. Below 90% in a stable market signals elevated risk.\nValue-add Business Plan:  Strategy to improve a property through renovations or management upgrades to raise rents and NOI, then sell at a higher valuation.\nGo / No-Go:  Final investment committee decision based on underwriting results, risk flag summary, and return targets vs. thresholds.",
      "lineHeight": 1.4
    },
